  "prompt": "Does India have the highest percentage of online trolls?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, studies and surveys indicate that India has a significant problem with online trolling and cyberbullying. However, it is challenging to definitively state that India has the highest percentage of online trolls compared to other countries, as this can vary based on different studies, methodologies, and definitions of trolling.\n\nVarious reports and surveys have highlighted that social media platforms in India are often rife with harassment and abusive behavior, which may suggest a high prevalence of trolling. Factors such as high internet penetration, the popularity of social media, and cultural attitudes towards online interaction can contribute to this phenomenon.\n\nNevertheless, similar issues are found in many countries around the world. Therefore, while India may have a significant incidence of online trolling, claiming it has the highest percentage would require more comprehensive and comparative data across different nations.",
